OL,3,CCould one of the UK's most iconic
OL,4,Cpebble beaches be replaced with sand?
OL,6,FOne resident said: "It's like that
OL,7,Fbecause the coastline has been formed
OL,8,Fover hundreds of thousands of years
OL,9,Fand after the ice age cut through to
OL,10,Fform the English channel the southern
OL,11,Fbeaches and the chalk cliffs are part
OL,12,Fof it. You'd need to change evolution.
OL,13,FIt's impossible to replace the pebbles
OL,14,Fwith sand."
OL,16,FAnother added: "Leave our beach alone
OL,17,F,all brightonians know and are used to
OL,18,Four pebbles if you don't like it go to
OL,19,FCamber Sands."
